<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="183" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,158,473]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">
<collectorName box="[136,262,158,185]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">In Martius’</collectorName>
protologue, the specimens on which this name is based are not specifically indicated. 
<collectorName box="[1249,1397,158,184]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">Nevertheless</collectorName>
, it is known that collections of 
<collectorName box="[430,517,194,220]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">Martius</collectorName>
are deposited in 
<collectorName box="[712,867,194,221]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">Herbarium M</collectorName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S." box="[882,1146,194,220]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" refId="ref8497" refString="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S. (1976 - 1988) Taxonomic Literature: A selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types, 2 nd ed., Smithsonian Libraries, last updated 28 Jun. 2012. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 48631" type="book" year="1976">Stafleu &amp; Cowan 1976</bibRefCitation>
–1988: 325). 
<bibRefCitation author="Cunha, M. C. S." box="[1296,1451,194,221]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" pagination="5 - 41" refId="ref7419" refString="Cunha, M. C. S. (1985) Revisao das especies do genero Luehea Willd. (Tiliaceae), ocorrentes no estado do Rio de Janeiro. Sellowia, Anais Botanicos do Herbario Barbosa Rodrigues 37: 5 - 41." type="journal article" year="1985">
<collectingCountry box="[1296,1369,194,220]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">Cunha</collectingCountry>
(1985)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned “ 
<emphasis box="[276,412,231,256]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">Martius s.n.</emphasis>
” (M) as the 
<typeStatus box="[562,663,230,256]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">holotype</typeStatus>
, specifying not to have seen it (“ 
<typeStatus box="[1040,1161,230,256]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">Holotypus</typeStatus>
– M, non vidi”), and not reporting any record number. This means that the status of the type needs to be corrected as 
<typeStatus box="[1146,1249,266,292]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">lectotype</typeStatus>
and considered as a first-step typification (Art. 9.17 of the ICN). Therefore, in accordance with Arts. 9.3 and 9.4 of the ICN, we designate herein the specimen 
<emphasis box="[374,511,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">Martius s.n.</emphasis>
(M0210173) as a second-step 
<typeStatus box="[867,970,338,364]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">lectotype</typeStatus>
by choosing the most complete specimen and one that is congruent with the protologue’s description. The specimen M0210174 is only a reproduction of Figure 61 from Martius’ work. Based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Cunha, M. C. S." box="[525,681,410,437]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" pagination="5 - 41" refId="ref7419" refString="Cunha, M. C. S. (1985) Revisao das especies do genero Luehea Willd. (Tiliaceae), ocorrentes no estado do Rio de Janeiro. Sellowia, Anais Botanicos do Herbario Barbosa Rodrigues 37: 5 - 41." type="journal article" year="1985">
<collectingCountry box="[525,598,410,436]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">Cunha</collectingCountry>
(1985)
</bibRefCitation>
and the present study, the application of the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1826" box="[1264,1424,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandiflora">
<emphasis box="[1264,1424,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">L. grandiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confirmed as an accepted species.
</paragraph>
